:"s"},{"role":"present_1mp","form":"نَتُكّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"present_1ms","form":"أَتُكّ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"},{"role":"past_1mp","form":"تَكَكْنا","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"p"},{"role":"past_1ms","form":"تَكَكْتُ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"p","per":"1","gen":"m","num":"s"}],"frequency_in_corpus":13,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":false}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to tick"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of تَكَّ (takka) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Onomatopoeic."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":null,"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%AA%D9%83/","headword_ar":"تك","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_36","lexicon_en":"Al-Ṣāḥib bin ʿAbbād, Al-Muḥīṭ fī l-Lugha (d. c. 995 CE)","lexicon_ar":"المحيط في اللغة للصاحب بن عباد","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=92099#89d6e3","body_html":"تك<br>التكَةُ: مَعْروفَةٌ، والجميع التكَكُ. وهو يَسْتَكِكُّ بالحَرِيْرِ.<br>والتّاكُّ: المَهْزُوْلُ من الإبل، تَك يَتِكَ ويَتُكُّ.<br>والتّاكُّ: الأحْمَقُ من الرجال، وقَوْمٌ تاكُوْنَ. وهو - أيضاً -: الذي يَتَكَلُّمُ بما يَدْري وما لا يَدْري وخَطَأًه أكْثَرُ من صَوَابِه. وهو بَين التَكَكِ والتكَّةِ: إذا كانَ مَطْروقاً في عَقْلِه.<br>وتَكَّ فلان من النَّبِيْذِ، وتكَّه النَّبِيْذُ: بَلَغَ منه.<br>وتكَّ الشَّيْءَ يَتُكُّه: إذا وَطئه حتى شَدَخَه.<br>وما في فيه حاكَّة ولا تاكَّةٌ: الحاكَّة الضِّرْسُ، والتَّاكَةُ النابُ. وتَكَّه تَكّاً: إذا قَطَعَه."},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_49","lexicon_en":"Arabic-English Lexicon by Edward William Lane (d. 1876)","lexicon_ar":"المعجم العربي الإنجليزي لإدوارد وليام لين","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=92099#ba8c3b","body_html":"<h3>تك</h3><span class=\"sense\">10</span> استتكّ التِّكَّةَ, (<abbr title=\"Abū Durayd, author of the Jamhara\">IDrd</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>,) or بِالتِّكَّةِ, (<abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>,) He inserted the تِكَّة in [the double upper border of] the drawers, or trousers. (<abbr title=\"Abū Durayd, author of the Jamhara\">IDrd</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) You say also, هُوَ يَسْتَتِكُ بِالحَرِيرِ He makes use of a تِكَّة of silk. (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>.) تِكَّةٌ The band [that is inserted in the double upper border] of the drawers, or trousers; (<abbr title=\"Abū Durayd, author of the Jamhara\">IDrd</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>;) [generally, a strip of cotton, which is often embroidered at each end; sometimes, of net-work; and] sometimes, of silk: (<abbr title=\"Asās al-Balāghah by al-Zamakhsharī\">A</abbr>:) <abbr title=\"Abū Durayd, author of the Jamhara\">IDrd</abbr> thinks it to be an adventitious word, though used in ancient times; (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>;) and <abbr title=\"Ibn-El-Ambáree (Abū al-Barakāt Kamāl al-Dīn ibn al-Anbārī)\">IAmb</abbr> says, I think it to be arabicized: (<abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>:) <abbr title=\"plural, جَمْعٌ\">pl.</abbr> تِكَكٌ. (<abbr title=\"The Ṣiḥāḥ (of al-Jawharī)\">S</abbr>, <abbr title=\"The Miṣbāḥ of al-Fayyūmī\">Msb</abbr>, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>.) مِتَكُّ The thing by means of which the تِكَّة is inserted in [the double upper border of] the drawers, or trousers. (<abbr title=\"The Tāj al-ʿArūs of Sayyid Murtaḍā al-Zabīdī\">TA</abbr>.) [It is generally a slender piece of wood, having at one end a loop through which a portion of the تكّة is passed.]\nQuasi تكأ تَكِئَ &amp;c.: see art. وكأ.\nQuasi تكل 1 تَكِلَ عَلَيْهِ, <abbr title=\"aorist (shows the vowel of the second consonant of the aorist/muḍāriʿ form)\">aor.</abbr> ـَ a <abbr title=\"dialect, لُغَةٌ\">dial.</abbr> var. of اِتَّكَلَ. (Ibn-'Abbád, <abbr title=\"al-Qāmūs al-Muḥīṭ of Firuzabadi\">K</abbr>) See art. وكل; where, also, see تُكَلَةٌ, &amp;c."}]}}